SNP_TRT : LKM Spark to Object Storage

COMPONENT NAME: LKM Spark Data Flow to Object Storage REST COMPONENT VERSION: 1 AUTHOR: Jerome Francoisse - jerome.francoisse@oracle.com COMPATIBILITY: ODI 12.1.3.0.1 or above
DESCRIPTION This KM will store data into Object Storage from a Spark Python variable and can be defined on the AP between the execution units, source technology Spark Python, target technology File. Currently only compatible with Object Storage as source.
PREREQUISITES - Create a Dataserver, a Physical Schema and a logical schema under the Spark Pthon technology. It doesn't have to be representing an actual Spark Cluster but it is used as the staging area in the mapping to allow the spark KMs to be used. - ConfigFilePath option : Reference your config file path to connect to OCI. More information : https://docs.oracle.com/en-us/iaas/Content/API/Concepts/sdkconfig.htm - FILE_LSCHEMA option : Reference a file logical schema pointing to the same location as the spark-work-dir properties in the Spark Dataserver definition - OS_LSCHEMA : Reference an OCI Object Storage logical schema that will be used to store the pyspark file used by the OCI Data Flow Application
